</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E7EFFF2FF3F7251DBB1FDAF" blockId="12.[192,1440,379,596]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B95344267E7EFFF2FF3F7251DE4FFE68" bold="true" box="[192,337,379,403]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Definition.</emphasis>
Not closely related to any other genus. Formerly placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E7EFFF2FBE77251DB47FE68" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1903" box="[1048,1113,379,403]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bolla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E7EFFF2FBE77251DB47FE68" box="[1048,1113,379,403]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Bolla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E7EFFF2FB987256DB83FE6F" box="[1127,1181,380,404]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E7EFFF2FB007251DE76FE4F" authority="Mabille, 1903" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bolla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pullata">
<emphasis id="B95344267E7EFFF2FB007251DABEFE68" box="[1279,1440,379,403]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Bolla pullata</emphasis>
Mabille, 1903
</taxonomicName>
, currently a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E7EFFF2FC9B72B1DA8CFE4F" authority="Godman and Salvin, [1896]" authorityName="Godman and Salvin" authorityYear="1896" box="[868,1426,411,436]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Staphylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imbras">
<emphasis id="B95344267E7EFFF2FC9B72B1DB22FE48" box="[868,1084,411,435]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Staphylus imbras</emphasis>
Godman and Salvin, [1896]
</taxonomicName>
), but is not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E7EFFF2FDD67291DD74FE28" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1903" box="[553,618,443,467]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bolla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E7EFFF2FDD67291DD74FE28" box="[553,618,443,467]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Bolla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E7EFFF2FD257296DC3DFE2F" box="[730,803,444,468]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[192,275,1906,1928]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,780,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[192,1440,779,1883]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Genomic trees of Carcharodini. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677243" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677243/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Keys to E. 
<quantity id="4CDF35D17E7EFFF2FC4B7296DB05FE2F" box="[948,1051,444,468]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.92988" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" unit="in" value="31.22">31.22 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E7EFFF2FBDC7296DBD6FE2F" author="Evans" box="[1059,1224,444,468]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" pagination="26 - 53" refId="ref27534" refString="Evans, W. H. 1953. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part III. Pyrginae. Section 2. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 246 p., pl. 26 - 53" type="book chapter" year="1953">Evans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
. Morphologically, distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E7EFFF2FE5572F1DEF5FE08" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1903" box="[426,491,475,499]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Bolla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E7EFFF2FE5572F1DEF5FE08" box="[426,491,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Bolla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by broad-ended valva without processes, but with concave costa ending with bulky ampulla weakly separated from short serrated harpe, and the lack of gray or ochreous overscaling on wings above. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly997.12.1:G125C, aly536.106.2:A2067G, aly127.74.3:A1567G, aly320.9.2:A806G, aly 
<date id="FF99BEF47E7EFFF2FC1A7116DB41FDAF" box="[997,1119,572,596]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" value="1011-11-01">1011.11.1</date>
:A34C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E7EFFF2FF3F7146DC0DFD1F" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E7EFFF2FF3F7146DA92FD78" blockId="12.[192,1420,620,644]" box="[192,1420,620,644]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B95344267E7EFFF2FF3F7146DE45FD7F" bold="true" box="[192,347,620,644]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name, a masculine noun in the nominative singular, echoes the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E7EFFF2FB597146DBC5FD7F" box="[1190,1243,620,644]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E7EFFF2FF3F71B1DDDDFD4F" blockId="12.[192,707,667,692]" box="[192,707,667,692]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B95344267E7EFFF2FF3F71B1DEB1FD48" bold="true" box="[192,431,667,691]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Species included.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E7EFFF2FDD771B6DD43FD4F" box="[552,605,668,692]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E7EFFF2FF3F71E6DC0DFD1F" blockId="12.[192,787,716,740]" box="[192,787,716,740]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B95344267E7EFFF2FF3F71E6DE62FD1F" bold="true" box="[192,380,716,740]" pageId="12" pageNumber="11">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E7EFFF2FE3371E6DC11FD1F" authority="Verity, 1940" authorityName="Verity" authorityYear="1940" box="[460,783,716,740]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Carcharodini">Carcharodini Verity, 1940</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
